WEBVTT

00:02.959 --> 00:04.613
- ♪ Hey, here comes Sunny
keeping it fun ♪

00:04.743 --> 00:06.310
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:06.441 --> 00:08.443
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:08.573 --> 00:10.140
♪ Hey

00:10.271 --> 00:11.968
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:12.099 --> 00:13.709
♪ Hair styling
with her best friends ♪

00:13.839 --> 00:16.059
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:16.190 --> 00:19.193
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny Day

00:19.323 --> 00:21.499
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:21.630 --> 00:23.284
- Whoo-hoo!

00:23.414 --> 00:28.028
- ♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:31.074
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.205 --> 00:33.468
♪ Having a sunny, sunny day

00:33.598 --> 00:34.599
- Hoo-hoo!

00:40.257 --> 00:43.130
[upbeat rock music]

00:43.260 --> 00:43.956
♪

00:44.087 --> 00:46.263
- This was the best day ever!

00:46.394 --> 00:49.658
Thanks for letting me tag along
while you styled Mandy's hair.

00:49.788 --> 00:51.181
- You're welcome, Junior.

00:51.312 --> 00:52.748
- I can't believe
we got to style

00:52.878 --> 00:54.837
a real pop star!

00:54.967 --> 00:56.360
Just look at her!

00:56.491 --> 00:59.624
- Ooh, that's my favorite.
- [giggles]

00:59.755 --> 01:00.886
- [gasps]
Stop!

01:01.017 --> 01:02.018
[brakes screech]

01:02.149 --> 01:03.628
[exciting music]

01:03.759 --> 01:05.282
- What's the matter, Junior?

01:05.413 --> 01:07.197
- Look, the circus is coming!

01:07.328 --> 01:09.286
This really is
the best day ever!

01:09.417 --> 01:11.201
- You made us stop the Glam Van

01:11.332 --> 01:13.769
just to show us a sign
for some circus?

01:13.899 --> 01:15.858
- Not   some  circus.

01:15.988 --> 01:20.645
Marvelous Martin's Magical
Traveling One-Ring Circus!

01:20.776 --> 01:24.910
- Wow... just look at it all.

01:25.041 --> 01:27.696
- Can we go? Can we go?
Can we? Please?

01:27.826 --> 01:30.438
- A day at the circus
is a great idea.

01:30.568 --> 01:32.918
What do you say we head to
the park to get tickets?

01:33.049 --> 01:33.919
- Yeah!
- All right!

01:34.050 --> 01:34.877
- Let's go!

01:35.007 --> 01:37.140
♪

01:37.271 --> 01:39.447
- Oh, thanks so much.

01:39.577 --> 01:41.666
Thanks for visiting
the Friendly Falls Park

01:41.797 --> 01:43.277
Theater Ticketing Service.

01:43.407 --> 01:44.365
How may I help you?

01:44.495 --> 01:45.496
- Timmy?

01:45.627 --> 01:47.368
You have another job?

01:47.498 --> 01:49.457
- Yup. All my life,
I've been a fan

01:49.587 --> 01:51.502
of the shows that come
to Friendly Falls,

01:51.633 --> 01:53.504
and now I'm a part of it!

01:53.635 --> 01:54.853
I give out the tickets.

01:54.984 --> 01:57.247
Ta-da!
- Nice gig.

01:57.378 --> 01:59.597
Bet you get to see
lots of great shows too.

01:59.728 --> 02:02.296
- Thing is, since I have to
be in the booth,

02:02.426 --> 02:05.516
I actually never get to see
any of the shows.

02:05.647 --> 02:07.692
But maybe someday, heh.

02:07.823 --> 02:09.433
So, what can I do for you?

02:09.564 --> 02:11.957
- We'd like five tickets
to Marvelous Martin's

02:12.088 --> 02:14.917
Magical Traveling
One-Ring Circus, please!

02:15.047 --> 02:16.310
- Circus?

02:16.440 --> 02:18.268
Mm. Uh, let's see.

02:18.399 --> 02:20.488
♪

02:20.618 --> 02:21.924
Mm, nope.

02:22.054 --> 02:23.578
Definitely no circus tickets
here.

02:23.708 --> 02:25.667
- But... it has to be there!

02:25.797 --> 02:26.885
We saw a sign.

02:27.016 --> 02:29.279
It has lions! Roar!

02:29.410 --> 02:31.499
- And clowns,
and a tightrope walker,

02:31.629 --> 02:32.761
and... whoa!

02:32.891 --> 02:33.936
- Come to think of it,

02:34.066 --> 02:35.938
the sign didn't say anything

02:36.068 --> 02:38.245
about it coming
to Friendly Falls.

02:38.375 --> 02:41.683
- It must be going
to other towns nearby.

02:41.813 --> 02:43.772
Sorry, Junior.

02:43.902 --> 02:46.078
- I was really looking forwardto it.

02:46.209 --> 02:47.950
- Don't be sad, Junior.

02:48.080 --> 02:50.822
I'm sure the circus will come
to Friendly Falls someday.

02:50.953 --> 02:52.911
- [gasps]
Really?

02:53.042 --> 02:54.739
Can you do that, Sunny?

02:54.870 --> 02:57.351
Get Marvelous Martin to
bring his circus here?

02:57.481 --> 02:58.787
- Here? Really?

02:58.917 --> 03:00.745
- Oh... I didn't mean that.

03:00.876 --> 03:02.138
I just--
- Sure!

03:02.269 --> 03:04.532
If anybody can do it,
Sunny can.

03:04.662 --> 03:06.273
She can do anything!

03:06.403 --> 03:08.188
- Way to go, Sunny!
- All right!

03:08.318 --> 03:13.367
- Well... I guess I could try
to call Marvelous Martin.

03:13.497 --> 03:14.977
He is the circus ringmaster,

03:15.107 --> 03:17.762
so maybe he could
bring his show here.

03:17.893 --> 03:19.547
- Yes!

03:19.677 --> 03:21.679
Sunny's bringing the circus
to Friendly Falls.

03:21.810 --> 03:23.768
- Hold on, Rox.
First, I have to--

03:23.899 --> 03:25.379
- Hey, everybody!

03:25.509 --> 03:27.294
The circus is coming!
The circus is coming!

03:27.424 --> 03:29.121
- Yes!
- Whoo-hoo!

03:29.252 --> 03:32.777
- All right!
- Yeah!

03:32.908 --> 03:35.737
- Well, looks like I'm bringing
the circus to town.

03:35.867 --> 03:37.434
♪

03:37.565 --> 03:41.003
Okay, just gotta call up
Marvelous Martin and ask him

03:41.133 --> 03:42.874
to bring his circus
to Friendly Falls.

03:43.005 --> 03:45.225
Easy-peasy, right?

03:45.355 --> 03:49.490
- Welcome, boys, girls,
children of all ages!

03:49.620 --> 03:52.014
You have reached
Marvelous Martin,

03:52.144 --> 03:56.148
ringmaster of the Magical
Traveling One-Ring Circus.

03:56.279 --> 03:58.150
- Hi, Mister!
Um, Marvelous.

03:58.281 --> 03:59.978
My name's Sunny, and--

04:00.109 --> 04:01.371
- When you hear the tone,
step right up

04:01.502 --> 04:03.852
and leave an amazing message!

04:03.982 --> 04:06.202
- Oh. Oh, uh... hi!

04:06.333 --> 04:07.421
My name is Sunny.

04:07.551 --> 04:09.074
I was hoping you could bring

04:09.205 --> 04:10.598
your one-ring circus
to Friendly Falls.

04:10.728 --> 04:12.382
Please call me back
as soon as you can.

04:12.513 --> 04:14.863
Thanks! And have a sunny day.

04:14.993 --> 04:16.952
I'm sure
he'll get back to me soon.

04:17.082 --> 04:18.475
- We just have to wait.

04:20.303 --> 04:24.089
♪

04:24.220 --> 04:25.395
[bell dings]

04:25.526 --> 04:26.440
- Whoa!
- Yes!

04:26.570 --> 04:27.919
- Hello?
- Sunny!

04:28.050 --> 04:30.270
- Oh.
Uh, hi, Cindy.

04:30.400 --> 04:32.402
- I just heard
you got the Magical Traveling

04:32.533 --> 04:34.143
One-Ring Circus
to come to town.

04:34.274 --> 04:35.971
- Well, actually, I--

04:36.101 --> 04:38.452
- I made a special dessert
just for the occasion.

04:38.582 --> 04:41.368
The ultimate one-ring donut!

04:41.498 --> 04:43.326
Like the one-ring circus.
Get it?

04:43.457 --> 04:45.459
all: [giggling]
- Ha, ha, ha!

04:45.589 --> 04:47.852
Hey, that's funny!

04:47.983 --> 04:49.332
I don't get it.

04:49.463 --> 04:51.421
- We have to get a hold
of that ringmaster.

04:51.552 --> 04:53.554
- I'll try calling him again.

04:53.684 --> 04:55.556
- Sunny, Sunny, Sunny!

04:55.686 --> 04:57.297
- The girl of the hour!

04:57.427 --> 04:58.863
- We heard you've been movin'
and shakin'

04:58.994 --> 05:00.387
to bring the circus to town.

05:00.517 --> 05:03.477
- Well, actually, I...
- Mm-mm.

05:03.607 --> 05:05.305
He's not answering.

05:05.435 --> 05:07.481
- Rox, can you try sending
Marvelous Martin a text?

05:07.611 --> 05:08.917
- On it!
- Sunny.

05:09.047 --> 05:10.440
You have to do my hair.

05:10.571 --> 05:12.268
This is gonna be the event
of the year!

05:12.399 --> 05:15.358
- I know!
I made one-ring donuts.

05:15.489 --> 05:17.882
- One-ring donuts?[laughs]

05:18.013 --> 05:19.667
Get it?

05:19.797 --> 05:20.885
'Cause if you do,
maybe you could

05:21.016 --> 05:22.452
explain it to me.

05:22.583 --> 05:25.237
- Anyway,
I'll need something fabulous.

05:25.368 --> 05:26.891
We have to be circus ready.

05:27.022 --> 05:28.719
- To be totally honest, Lacey,

05:28.850 --> 05:31.853
I'm still waiting for Marvelous
Martin to call me back, so--

05:31.983 --> 05:33.507
- Marvelous! Yes!

05:33.637 --> 05:35.900
That's exactly the word
I want people to say

05:36.031 --> 05:37.249
when they see my hair.

05:37.380 --> 05:38.512
I'll give you some timeto think

05:38.642 --> 05:39.948
of something great for me.

05:40.078 --> 05:41.471
- And me!

05:41.602 --> 05:43.125
- I better go make more donuts.

05:43.255 --> 05:45.301
This is gonna be some show.

05:45.432 --> 05:46.302
See you later.

05:46.433 --> 05:48.304
- Bye! Well?

05:48.435 --> 05:49.697
- I texted him.

05:49.827 --> 05:50.959
No answer.

05:51.089 --> 05:52.743
- Aww.
- Now what?

05:52.874 --> 05:54.484
- Hey, Sunny, check it out!

05:54.615 --> 05:55.920
I spent all morning
making these tickets

05:56.051 --> 05:57.269
for today's circus.

05:57.400 --> 05:58.836
- Today's circus?

05:58.967 --> 06:01.143
- Timmy's giving them out,
and guess what?

06:01.273 --> 06:02.536
Everyone's coming--
this circus

06:02.666 --> 06:04.320
is gonna be big, big, big!

06:04.451 --> 06:06.148
All right!

06:06.278 --> 06:07.323
- Oh, boy.

06:09.847 --> 06:13.111
[phone beeps, chirps]

06:13.242 --> 06:14.678
- You have reached
Marvelous...

06:14.809 --> 06:18.029
- Ugh, we have to get a hold
of Marvelous Martin!

06:18.160 --> 06:20.336
- I'm sending him
another text...

06:20.467 --> 06:23.252
this time with lots
of cute pictures.

06:23.383 --> 06:26.647
Heart. Happy face.
Pizza slice.

06:26.777 --> 06:27.952
There!

06:28.083 --> 06:30.085
No way he won't answer
that one.

06:30.215 --> 06:31.826
- How's the email coming,
Doodle?

06:31.956 --> 06:33.567
- Not great.

06:33.697 --> 06:36.047
Paws aren't exactly built
for this kind of thing.

06:36.178 --> 06:38.746
"Either mix took a wag."

06:38.876 --> 06:40.312
Do you think he'll understand?

06:40.443 --> 06:43.228
Because I typed it,
and I don't understand.

06:43.359 --> 06:45.230
- Hi, Timmy.
- Hey, guys.

06:45.361 --> 06:47.494
You'll never guess
who needed their hat repaired.

06:47.624 --> 06:50.279
Marvelous Martin,
the ringmaster!

06:50.410 --> 06:52.063
- You're kidding!
- No way.

06:52.194 --> 06:53.761
- Can I stop typing now?

06:53.891 --> 06:55.458
- Wait, you repair hats?

06:55.589 --> 06:56.546
- Uh-huh.

06:56.677 --> 06:58.330
I've always liked hats.

06:58.461 --> 07:01.333
Party hats, cowboy hats,
top hats...

07:01.464 --> 07:02.944
all kinds of hats!

07:03.074 --> 07:04.554
So I learned to repair them.

07:04.685 --> 07:06.164
- That's great!

07:06.295 --> 07:07.905
But the part
about Marvelous Martin?

07:08.036 --> 07:09.429
- Oh. Yes.

07:09.559 --> 07:11.343
So, Marvelous Martin
came to me

07:11.474 --> 07:12.997
with an emergency.

07:13.128 --> 07:15.652
He needed me
to re-stitch his top hat.

07:15.783 --> 07:18.263
- Wow!
Okay, we need details.

07:18.394 --> 07:21.266
- Well, it's a classic
ringmaster's hat

07:21.397 --> 07:23.617
about this high
with silk lining and--

07:23.747 --> 07:25.923
- No! Not about the hat.

07:26.054 --> 07:28.317
About where we can find
Marvelous Martin.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.406
We've been trying all day.

07:30.537 --> 07:32.539
- Oh, he's picking up
his order tomorrow.

07:32.669 --> 07:35.019
Until then,
he said he's staying

07:35.150 --> 07:37.369
at the hotel
just outside of town.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.589
- Perfect!
I can go to the hotel right now

07:39.720 --> 07:41.373
and ask Marvelous Martin
to bring his circus

07:41.504 --> 07:42.723
to Friendly Falls!

07:42.853 --> 07:44.420
I'll be back
before you know it.

07:44.551 --> 07:46.204
Thanks, Timmy!

07:46.335 --> 07:47.684
- Good luck!
- Good luck!

07:47.815 --> 07:54.865
♪

07:56.519 --> 07:58.478
- Hello, there.
Can I help you?

07:58.608 --> 08:01.045
- Hi. I'm looking
for Marvelous Martin.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.612
- Oh, I'm sorry.

08:02.743 --> 08:04.396
Marvelous Martin gave me
strict instructions

08:04.527 --> 08:06.094
he's not to be disturbed.

08:06.224 --> 08:08.009
- Please? I have to
get in touch with him.

08:08.139 --> 08:09.837
It's really important.

08:09.967 --> 08:11.012
It'll just take a second.

08:11.142 --> 08:12.840
- Sorry. Rules are rules.

08:12.970 --> 08:14.842
- See, everyone
in Friendly Falls

08:14.972 --> 08:17.453
is counting on me
to bring the circus to town,

08:17.584 --> 08:20.630
and if I can't,
they'll be so disappointed.

08:20.761 --> 08:21.979
Please, can I speak with him?

08:22.110 --> 08:24.112
- Sorry. No can do.

08:24.242 --> 08:27.202
- Well... can you please
have him call me?

08:27.332 --> 08:28.856
Here's my name and number.

08:30.379 --> 08:32.076
- Sunny. Will do.

08:32.207 --> 08:34.731
- Thanks.
- Have a good day.

08:34.862 --> 08:39.083
♪

08:39.214 --> 08:42.565
[upbeat music]

08:42.696 --> 08:44.654
- This is so exciting!

08:44.785 --> 08:46.656
- Sunny?
- She's back!

08:46.787 --> 08:49.616
- Guys... I'm afraid I have
some bad news.

08:49.746 --> 08:52.227
I tried,
but I couldn't get in touch

08:52.357 --> 08:53.707
with Marvelous Martin.

08:53.837 --> 08:55.056
It looks like the circus

08:55.186 --> 08:56.840
won't be coming
to Friendly Falls.

08:56.971 --> 08:59.147
- No circus?
- No!

08:59.277 --> 09:01.105
- I know
everybody's disappointed,

09:01.236 --> 09:03.107
but if we put our heads
together,

09:03.238 --> 09:04.935
I'm sure there's something
we can do.

09:05.066 --> 09:06.720
- That's okay, Sunny...
I mean,

09:06.850 --> 09:09.200
it's not like you could
just find a new circus.

09:09.331 --> 09:11.681
- Hmm... that's it!

09:11.812 --> 09:16.294
Maybe I can't find one,
but we can make one.

09:16.425 --> 09:19.210
What if we put on
our own circus, together?

09:19.341 --> 09:21.082
- You're kidding, right?

09:21.212 --> 09:22.910
Because we're not performers.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.825
We're just regular folks.

09:24.955 --> 09:27.305
Or at least all of you are.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.917
- Sunny's right.
I think it could work.

09:30.047 --> 09:31.527
- That's the spirit, Rox.

09:31.658 --> 09:32.876
Think about it.

09:33.007 --> 09:34.878
We all have
our own special talents.

09:35.009 --> 09:36.314
I can be ringmaster.

09:36.445 --> 09:38.142
- Ooh!
I can walk the tightrope!

09:38.273 --> 09:39.753
- Ooh, I'll be the clown!
[horn honks]

09:39.883 --> 09:41.363
- I can run the snack bar.

09:41.493 --> 09:43.887
- Hey, Sunny,
can I be in the circus too?

09:44.018 --> 09:46.455
I've always dreamed
of riding a unicycle.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.500
- Go for it.
- Great!

09:48.631 --> 09:50.938
Now all I need to do
is find a unicycle

09:51.068 --> 09:52.330
and learn how to ride it.

09:52.461 --> 09:55.029
- See?
It's coming together already.

09:55.159 --> 09:57.640
- Putting on our own circus
is a great idea.

09:57.771 --> 09:59.555
I'm not saying
our Hula-Hoop act

09:59.686 --> 10:01.731
is the best Hula-Hoop act ever,
but--

10:01.862 --> 10:02.993
- It really is.

10:03.124 --> 10:03.994
- Come on!
It's rehearsal time.

10:04.125 --> 10:05.343
- Whoa!

10:05.474 --> 10:07.389
- This is gonna be
the best circus ever.

10:07.519 --> 10:08.390
I'll spread the word.

10:08.520 --> 10:09.521
- See you later, Sunny.

10:09.652 --> 10:10.522
- Let's go!

10:10.653 --> 10:11.741
- Come on, Blair.

10:11.872 --> 10:12.742
Let's go get some supplies.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.396
- All right!

10:14.526 --> 10:16.528
- So, think there might be
a spot in the show

10:16.659 --> 10:19.793
for a dog
with my unique talents?

10:19.923 --> 10:22.317
Something like... this?

10:22.447 --> 10:23.971
And a-one, and a-two,

10:24.101 --> 10:26.669
and a-whoa, whoa, whoa!

10:26.800 --> 10:28.540
♪

10:28.671 --> 10:30.934
- Hang on.
I've got an idea!

10:31.065 --> 10:33.197
I have the perfect role
for you, Doodle.

10:33.328 --> 10:35.199
- Ooh? What? What?Tell me!

10:35.330 --> 10:36.766
- I'm not gonna tell you.

10:36.897 --> 10:38.202
I'm gonna show you!

10:38.333 --> 10:40.857
Trust me, it'll be great.

10:40.988 --> 10:42.772
♪

10:42.903 --> 10:47.734
Some hair pins...
some hair extensions...

10:47.864 --> 10:51.041
♪

10:51.172 --> 10:53.391
A little back-combing...

10:53.522 --> 10:56.568
and a few extensions
under your chin.

10:56.699 --> 10:58.875
♪

10:59.006 --> 11:00.747
And with a little ribbon,

11:00.877 --> 11:05.360
I'm going to give you
a real lion tail!

11:05.490 --> 11:07.536
- I'm the circus lion!

11:07.667 --> 11:10.060
Roar! Roar, roar, roar!

11:10.191 --> 11:12.367
I love it!

11:12.497 --> 11:14.891
- Smile!
- Roar!

11:15.022 --> 11:17.589
- Now, that's one
for the Style Files!

11:17.720 --> 11:19.243
- When do I go on?

11:19.374 --> 11:21.506
- When it's your turn,
I'll give you this cue.

11:23.508 --> 11:25.206
- Snap and point. Got it!

11:25.336 --> 11:27.425
♪

11:27.556 --> 11:28.818
- Wow!

11:28.949 --> 11:31.212
We have our very own lion.

11:31.342 --> 11:33.127
- [laughs]
Cool!

11:33.257 --> 11:34.345
- Okay, team.

11:34.476 --> 11:36.826
Ready... set...

11:36.957 --> 11:39.002
all: Gear up and go!

11:39.133 --> 11:45.008
♪

11:45.139 --> 11:46.880
[engine turns over]

11:47.010 --> 11:53.060
♪

11:55.584 --> 11:56.541
- Wow.

11:56.672 --> 11:58.630
The stage looks amazing!

11:58.761 --> 12:01.459
Thanks everyone
for working so hard

12:01.590 --> 12:04.636
and being part of the very
first Friendly Falls circus!

12:04.767 --> 12:06.595
- Let's go!
- [laughs]

12:06.726 --> 12:08.510
- Whoo!
- This is so exciting!

12:08.640 --> 12:10.642
- Now it's time to see
what you've got.

12:10.773 --> 12:12.601
Rox, why don't we
start with you?

12:12.732 --> 12:15.604
- Well, I was planning on
being a tightrope walker,

12:15.735 --> 12:18.259
but there's one tiny problem.

12:18.389 --> 12:19.651
I don't have a tightrope.

12:19.782 --> 12:21.044
- Hmm.

12:21.175 --> 12:22.829
Good thing we brought
my Glam-a-Go-Go.

12:22.959 --> 12:25.353
♪

12:25.483 --> 12:29.487
How about if I...
twist some ribbons to make

12:29.618 --> 12:32.664
an extra-strong tightrope...

12:32.795 --> 12:36.233
and tie it
to these apple boxes?

12:36.364 --> 12:38.322
♪

12:38.453 --> 12:40.150
- Perfect! Thanks, Sunny.

12:40.281 --> 12:41.108
Okay.

12:41.238 --> 12:42.500
♪

12:42.631 --> 12:43.632
[grunts]

12:43.763 --> 12:45.721
♪

12:45.852 --> 12:48.419
Eyes on the prize.
Eyes on the prize.

12:48.550 --> 12:50.291
♪

12:50.421 --> 12:53.903
Eyes... on... the... prize.
Whoa!

12:54.034 --> 12:55.557
[giggles]

12:55.687 --> 12:57.646
Maybe I should have kept
my eyes on the tightrope.

12:57.777 --> 13:00.083
- [laughs]
Just keep practicing.

13:00.214 --> 13:01.519
You'll get it.

13:01.650 --> 13:04.392
Okay, who's next?
- [grunts]

13:04.522 --> 13:07.264
- Hey!
- Sorry.

13:07.395 --> 13:09.571
- I just heard a crash.
Was that my cue?

13:09.701 --> 13:11.138
- No, Doodle.

13:11.268 --> 13:12.879
Your cue is a snap and point.

13:13.009 --> 13:14.097
Remember?

13:14.228 --> 13:15.533
- Of course. Snap and point.

13:15.664 --> 13:16.926
Snap and point.
I got it!

13:17.057 --> 13:18.885
Uh, I mean... roar!

13:19.015 --> 13:20.060
- [laughs]

13:21.844 --> 13:23.106
- [gasps]

13:23.237 --> 13:24.281
♪

13:24.412 --> 13:25.892
Our hoops are broken!

13:26.022 --> 13:27.719
Now how are we
supposed to perform

13:27.850 --> 13:29.896
our juggling extravaganza?

13:30.026 --> 13:33.813
- Don't worry.
We can find a way to fix this.

13:33.943 --> 13:35.684
Some scrunchies.
- Huh?

13:35.815 --> 13:37.729
♪

13:37.860 --> 13:41.995
- A little hair spray,
and all fixed.

13:43.692 --> 13:45.302
- [grunting]

13:47.130 --> 13:48.566
Well... it didn't break.

13:48.697 --> 13:50.307
- Whoo!
- Coming through!

13:50.438 --> 13:52.092
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

13:52.222 --> 13:53.571
Whoa!

13:53.702 --> 13:57.358
- Great act, Timmy.
How does it end?

13:57.488 --> 13:58.925
- I-I'm not sure.

13:59.055 --> 14:01.362
Uh, I don't know how to stop.

14:01.492 --> 14:02.842
Whoa!
[loud crash]

14:02.972 --> 14:04.974
- Is that my cue?

14:05.105 --> 14:06.367
- No, Doodle!

14:06.497 --> 14:08.804
Snap and point.

14:08.935 --> 14:10.980
- Hey, look.
We're gettin' the hang of this.

14:11.111 --> 14:13.591
- Whoa!

14:13.722 --> 14:15.202
Sort of!

14:15.332 --> 14:18.379
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

14:18.509 --> 14:22.383
- Whew... putting together
a circus is thirsty work.

14:22.513 --> 14:23.384
I need a glass of water.

14:23.514 --> 14:24.994
- Did you say water?

14:25.125 --> 14:26.778
[horn honks]

14:26.909 --> 14:27.910
- [laughs]

14:28.041 --> 14:29.651
- Part of my new clown act.

14:29.781 --> 14:30.913
And check this out.

14:33.481 --> 14:34.656
- Ooh!

14:37.354 --> 14:39.791
Hey! That's me!

14:39.922 --> 14:41.793
Cool!

14:41.924 --> 14:44.013
- Whoa!

14:44.144 --> 14:45.232
- Are you okay, Blair?

14:45.362 --> 14:46.450
- I'm great!

14:46.581 --> 14:48.975
And I'm gonna add that
to my act.

14:49.105 --> 14:52.021
Whoa... oh!

14:52.152 --> 14:54.023
- Whoa!

14:54.154 --> 14:57.070
[dramatic music]

14:57.200 --> 14:59.115
♪

14:59.246 --> 15:00.508
- Oh, no.

15:00.638 --> 15:03.424
♪

15:03.554 --> 15:05.861
- Is that my cue?

15:05.992 --> 15:07.515
- Whoa-oh-oh! Whoa!

15:07.645 --> 15:08.646
[loud crash]

15:08.777 --> 15:09.821
- [groans]

15:13.738 --> 15:15.871
- So much for Friendly Falls'
first circus.

15:16.002 --> 15:18.091
- The show starts
in less than an hour,

15:18.221 --> 15:21.659
and we're in even worse shape
than we started.

15:21.790 --> 15:23.574
- We'll never be ready in time.

15:23.705 --> 15:25.185
- Never say never!

15:25.315 --> 15:27.187
We can still put on
a great show.

15:27.317 --> 15:29.363
- Eyes on the prize!
- Right!

15:29.493 --> 15:30.364
all: Yeah!

15:30.494 --> 15:37.153
♪

15:39.764 --> 15:41.244
- There.

15:41.375 --> 15:42.376
Come on, guys.

15:44.987 --> 15:46.206
See, guys?

15:46.336 --> 15:48.077
I told you
we could make it happen.

15:48.208 --> 15:49.687
- And just in time.

15:49.818 --> 15:52.386
Look!
The audience is already here.

15:52.516 --> 15:53.865
- All right!
- [laughs]

15:53.996 --> 15:56.216
- One-ring donuts!
- Over here.

15:56.346 --> 15:58.261
- Get your one-ring donuts!

15:58.392 --> 16:00.394
- Welcome, one and all,

16:00.524 --> 16:03.397
to the first-ever
Friendly Falls Circus!

16:03.527 --> 16:05.486
- Oh, wow!

16:05.616 --> 16:07.618
- ♪ Come together, everyone

16:07.749 --> 16:09.881
- ♪ Step right up
and join the fun ♪

16:10.012 --> 16:11.840
- ♪ Get ready for thrills
and cheer ♪

16:11.971 --> 16:15.104
singers: ♪ Hey, hey, hey,
the circus is here ♪

16:15.235 --> 16:17.106
- Whoo-hoo![laughs]

16:17.237 --> 16:19.630
- Come on!
singers: ♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh

16:19.761 --> 16:21.284
- ♪ There's a clown
that will make you ♪

16:21.415 --> 16:22.503
♪ Laugh out loud

16:22.633 --> 16:24.070
singers: ♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh

16:24.200 --> 16:26.202
- ♪ And a daredevil
with amazing crowd ♪

16:26.333 --> 16:27.856
singers: ♪ Oh, oh, oh

16:27.987 --> 16:30.250
- ♪ There is so much we'll do

16:30.380 --> 16:32.643
- ♪ Like ride a unicycle!
- ♪ And juggle hoops!

16:32.774 --> 16:34.471
- Whoa!

16:34.602 --> 16:36.169
singers: ♪ Whoa-oh-oh

16:36.299 --> 16:38.736
- ♪ Watch the tumbling act
rip back on stage ♪

16:38.867 --> 16:40.303
singers: ♪ Whoa-oh-oh

16:40.434 --> 16:42.958
- ♪ And the lion tricks
are on display ♪

16:43.089 --> 16:44.960
singers: ♪ Come together,
everyone ♪

16:45.091 --> 16:47.093
♪ Step right up
and join the fun ♪

16:47.223 --> 16:49.095
♪ Get ready for thrills
and cheer ♪

16:49.225 --> 16:51.401
♪ Hey, hey, hey,
the circus is here ♪

16:51.532 --> 16:53.316
- ♪ Come together, everyone

16:53.447 --> 16:55.275
singers: ♪ Hey, hey, hey,
the circus is here ♪

16:55.405 --> 16:57.190
- ♪ Step right up
and join the fun ♪

16:57.320 --> 17:00.149
singers: ♪ Hey, hey, hey,
the circus is here ♪

17:00.280 --> 17:02.847
[cheers and applause]

17:02.978 --> 17:05.285
- Excuse me.
Do you know where I can find--

17:05.415 --> 17:07.678
- Shh. The show's starting.

17:07.809 --> 17:09.506
- For our first act,

17:09.637 --> 17:13.162
let's bring out...
the Amazing Rox!

17:13.293 --> 17:15.556
[cheers and applause]

17:15.686 --> 17:19.299
- Steady... steady.

17:19.429 --> 17:20.996
Whoa!

17:21.127 --> 17:22.824
[crowd gasps]

17:22.954 --> 17:24.913
Whoa!

17:25.044 --> 17:27.350
- Nice tight walk!
- Yeah!

17:27.481 --> 17:29.265
- Thank you!

17:29.396 --> 17:32.355
- And now let's have
a big Friendly Falls welcome

17:32.486 --> 17:34.923
for Blair the Clown!

17:37.795 --> 17:39.493
- Hello, everybody!

17:39.623 --> 17:42.670
[laughter]

17:42.800 --> 17:46.369
Uh, whoopsie!
[chuckles]

17:46.500 --> 17:48.415
- There you go. Enjoy.

17:48.545 --> 17:51.548
- Pick a card, any card.
- Hmm.

17:51.679 --> 17:53.550
- Whoa! Whoa.

17:53.681 --> 17:56.945
Um, your card was definitely
one of those.

17:57.076 --> 17:59.904
[laughter and applause]

18:01.732 --> 18:04.300
Go ahead.
Give it a sniff.

18:04.431 --> 18:07.825
- Oh! She got me!
[laughs]

18:07.956 --> 18:09.827
♪

18:09.958 --> 18:11.655
- Thank you, Blair the Clown.

18:11.786 --> 18:13.788
- Thank you, thank you!

18:13.918 --> 18:15.964
Oh, stop it.
Thank you!

18:16.095 --> 18:17.835
[cane whoops]

18:17.966 --> 18:20.360
- [laughs] And now,
give it up for

18:20.490 --> 18:23.841
Lacey and KC
and their dazzling hoops.

18:23.972 --> 18:25.191
- Let's show 'em how it's done.

18:25.321 --> 18:27.758
♪

18:27.889 --> 18:29.847
[cheers and applause]

18:29.978 --> 18:32.720
♪

18:32.850 --> 18:34.635
- Look at her go!

18:34.765 --> 18:36.767
- Ha! Ha!
- [grunts]

18:36.898 --> 18:38.552
[cheers and applause]

18:38.682 --> 18:40.858
[KC barks]

18:40.989 --> 18:42.817
- Yay, Lacey!
- Look at KC go!

18:42.947 --> 18:44.906
- Whoo-hoo!
- Whoa!

18:45.036 --> 18:47.778
- One hoop...
and another hoop...

18:47.909 --> 18:49.519
and another hoop!

18:49.650 --> 18:53.262
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

18:53.393 --> 18:54.785
Thank you so much.

18:54.916 --> 18:57.571
- Oh-ho-ho! Wow!

18:57.701 --> 18:59.138
Incredible!

18:59.268 --> 19:00.443
- Uh-huh. I know.

19:00.574 --> 19:02.445
We're great. Louder!

19:02.576 --> 19:05.013
Let's hear it. Thank you.
Thank you very much.

19:05.144 --> 19:07.058
- And now for our next act...

19:07.189 --> 19:08.886
- Sorry, Sunny!
Couldn't wait!

19:09.017 --> 19:11.062
Watch out!
Comin' through.

19:11.193 --> 19:14.414
Whoa! Whoa!

19:14.544 --> 19:17.025
Whoa!

19:17.156 --> 19:19.158
- Oh, no! Watch out!

19:19.288 --> 19:21.682
- Whoa. Look out!

19:22.726 --> 19:26.295
Oh... whoo!

19:26.426 --> 19:27.775
Oh-ho!
[chuckles]

19:27.905 --> 19:29.124
[cheers and applause]

19:29.255 --> 19:33.259
- Incredible! Wow!
I love this show.

19:35.609 --> 19:37.437
- Whoo! Hey, thank you.

19:37.567 --> 19:40.091
- And now for the big finale...

19:40.222 --> 19:43.834
the frightening...
the ferocious...

19:43.965 --> 19:46.489
Doodle the Lion!

19:46.620 --> 19:47.621
- Yeah!

19:47.751 --> 19:48.839
Yahoo!

19:48.970 --> 19:50.058
Go, lion! Go, lion!

19:50.189 --> 19:53.104
- Doodle, that's your cue!

19:53.235 --> 19:55.368
- Oh, right.

19:55.498 --> 19:57.500
Ha-ha! Yahoo!

19:57.631 --> 20:01.330
Roar! Roar, roar, roar!

20:01.461 --> 20:02.723
- Amazing!

20:02.853 --> 20:05.029
[upbeat music]

20:05.160 --> 20:07.858
both: ♪ Sunny and Doodle,
Doodle and Sunny ♪

20:07.989 --> 20:10.078
♪ We go together
like bees and honey ♪

20:10.209 --> 20:12.689
♪ Like butter on bread
or a tail on a bunny ♪

20:12.820 --> 20:15.475
♪ Sunny and Doodle,
Doodle and Sunny ♪

20:15.605 --> 20:16.867
- Roar!

20:16.998 --> 20:18.478
Roar, roar, roar!

20:18.608 --> 20:21.176
- I've seen a lot of lions
in my day,

20:21.307 --> 20:24.484
but I've never seen a lion
do that before!

20:24.614 --> 20:25.963
Bravo.

20:26.094 --> 20:28.357
- He's not a real lion.[laughs]

20:28.488 --> 20:29.880
- [laughs]

20:30.011 --> 20:32.535
[cheers and applause]

20:34.407 --> 20:37.236
- Yeah!
Go, Friendly Falls Circus!

20:37.366 --> 20:39.934
- Thank you.
Thanks for coming.

20:40.064 --> 20:42.153
Bye!

20:42.284 --> 20:43.894
That was awesome!

20:44.025 --> 20:45.983
We sure make a good team.

20:46.114 --> 20:47.333
- But we couldn't
have done it

20:47.463 --> 20:50.074
without our ringmaster Sunny!

20:50.205 --> 20:52.816
- Best circus ever!
- Roar!

20:52.947 --> 20:55.776
- [gasps]
- Marvelous Martin?

20:55.906 --> 20:57.386
What are you doing here?

20:57.517 --> 21:00.520
- I've been trying to reach you
for hours!

21:00.650 --> 21:03.305
You're a hard person
to get a hold of.

21:03.436 --> 21:06.395
- [laughs]
That makes two of us.

21:06.526 --> 21:09.180
- I came to tell you
that I'd be happy

21:09.311 --> 21:12.706
to bring my circus
to Friendly Falls.

21:12.836 --> 21:14.229
- Thank you very much
for the offer,

21:14.360 --> 21:16.405
Marvelous Martin,
but we have our own

21:16.536 --> 21:18.059
amazing circus here already.

21:18.189 --> 21:20.801
- [laughs]
I guess you're right.

21:20.931 --> 21:24.979
Well, you'd all be welcome
to join my circus any day.

21:25.109 --> 21:27.373
Now, where's that boy
with my hat?

21:27.503 --> 21:29.200
- Watch out!
Coming through!

21:29.331 --> 21:31.377
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

21:31.507 --> 21:34.597
- Bravo!
- Stop me! Stop me!

21:34.728 --> 21:35.946
[loud crash]

21:38.122 --> 21:39.559
I'm okay!

21:42.213 --> 21:43.693
- Hi! It's me, Sunny,

21:43.824 --> 21:46.217
with another look
inside the Style Files.

21:46.348 --> 21:48.829
What an amazing lion style!

21:48.959 --> 21:50.221
Wow!

21:50.352 --> 21:51.875
For this hairstyle and more,

21:52.006 --> 21:53.616
check out Sunny's Style Files

21:53.747 --> 21:56.880
at NickJr.com
and the Nick Jr. app.

21:57.011 --> 21:59.230
Keep smilin'.
Keep stylin'.

22:05.324 --> 22:08.631
[upbeat dance music]

22:08.762 --> 22:15.377
♪
